************************************************************************************************************************************************************************

Harris and Shi-Thomasi algorithm.
key-point detection.

running instructions:

1. Open the Harris and Shi-Thomasi.ipynb file in jupyter notebook
2. In the second cell, at line 1: imgColor = cv2.imread('monument1.png') - give input image path at place of dummy input image path(here in e.g. it is 'monument1.png')
3. start the kernel and execute the file
4. Output will be shown and saved in the working directory

************************************************************************************************************************************************************************

SIFT - Scale-invariant feature transform.
Scale Invariant keypoint detection algorithm.

running instructions:

1. Open the SIFT.ipynb file in jupyter notebook
2. In the second cell, at line 1: imgColor = cv2.imread('monument1.png') -  give input image path at place of dummy input image path(here in e.g. it is 'monument1.png')
3. start the kernel and execute the file
4. Output will be shown and saved in the working directory

